# Skyrocket update after 3 weeks

21st May 2026

YinYin Chiu
Software Engineer, Oursky
yinyinchiu@oursky.com

## Recap

Skyrocket is built for
- Setup a env / tool for colleagues to deploy their application

## Previously

Limitation
- Way of cli installation sucks
- Need docker installed in user's machine
- Assume Dockerfile exists
- Not support image size > 2Gi
- Only support single service

## Previously

Future milestones
- Migrate away from fly.io
- Multi services support
- Configuration (Secrets config) support
- Postgresql & redis support (Hopefully happen in this month, ping Big Cal)
- Move away build pipeline from user's machine
- Support Github PR preview
- Deploy (or maybe migrate??) via mcp

## Today

- Way of cli installation sucks -> still sucks but better
- No need docker installed in user's machine
- Still assume Dockerfile exists
- ~~Not support image size > 2Gi~~
  - Expect source code (docker context) < 500mb
- Moved away build pipeline from user's machine
- Changed to poll base

## Today

- Support Postgresql, redis and s3
- Support secrets management
- Support multi services
  - Separate Dockerfile and context
  - Support nested dockerignore
- Support use public docker images
- Predeploy tasks
  - DB migration
  - Insert seed
  - Conditional

## Today

- Created a documentation site [https://docs-skyrocket.oursky.dev/](https://docs-skyrocket.oursky.dev/)
- Included a llm-full.txt [https://docs-skyrocket.oursky.dev/llms-full.txt](https://docs-skyrocket.oursky.dev/llms-full.txt)

